Bart vs. Lisa vs. The Third Grade

3
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:18,380
[BELL RINGING]

4
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:24,940
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

5
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:30,540
[BEEPING]

6
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:41,150
[LISA PLAYS SOLO]

7
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,230
D'oh! Ah!

8
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,810
[GRUNTS]

9
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:31,580
<i>[TRIBAL MUSIC PLAYING]</i>

10
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,060
MAN [ON TV]:
<i>Welcome back</i>

11
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,800
<i>to </i>Animal Survivor.

12
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:36,570
[MONKEY GIBBERING]

13
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:39,100
Okay, tribes, it's been a rough week.

14
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,730
Rhino,
you lost the tribe's fishing equipment.

15
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,540
[GROANS]

16
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:47,050
And we saw a dramatic collapse
in the lion-gazelle alliance.

17
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,870
[ROARS]

18
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,110
Oh, I hate reality shows.

19
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:55,580
A year ago, you said they were the
greatest thing that ever happened to us.

20
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,850
I've grown. You haven't.

21
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:01,280
<i>And now we're back to</i>
Touch the Stove.

22
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:04,580
So, Kevin,
I hear you collect amusing postcards.

23
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,950
Uh, yeah, it all started when...

24
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:09,330
HOST: Touch the stove.
- Aah!

25
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,380
I can't take any more of these shows.

26
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:14,330
If I wanted reality,
I'd finally have this lump looked at.

27
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:19,690
Networks love reality shows because
they don't have to pay writers or actors.

28
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:23,580
Stupid writers and actors, priced
yourselves right out of the business.

29
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,920
Nice going, geniuses.

30
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,970
Let's get one of those satellite dishes.

31
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,400
Then we can stop suckling
on the six-network teat.

32
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:34,360
Get back, honky cat.
Those systems are too expensive.

33
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,930
Marge, we can't pinch pennies
on the machine...

34
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,080
...that's going to be raising
our children.

35
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:44,090
Come on, kids. Daddy knows a way
to get some money with no risk.

36
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:46,850
[TRUMPET PLAYING
AND AUDIENCE CHEERING]

37
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:49,920
ANNOUNCER:
<i>And the winner by a nose is No Risk.</i>

38
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:51,880
Woo-hoo!

39
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:57,740
Okay. Now all we have to do
is install your satellite dish.

40
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,250
Can you be home
from 8 a.m. Monday morning...

41
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:02,440
- ...through June?
- No problem.

42
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:08,360
Hey, Flanders,
check out my new satellite dish.

43
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:09,800
[WHISTLES]

44
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,840
Boy, that's jim-dandy roof candy.

45
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:14,310
I'd love to come over
and watch that Church Channel.

46
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:17,050
- I bet you would.
- Oh, you'd win that bet.

47
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:19,730
I'm spending all my money
on religious pay-per-view.

48
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,200
Or as I like to call it, "pray-per-view."

49
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,610
Damn your sparkling wordplay.

50
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,450
And bless your humble home.

51
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,000
[GRUMBLES]

52
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:31,100
Oh, it's red wire to red wire.

53
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,480
[SCOFFS]

54
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,550
What idiot dreamed that up?

55
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:37,750
And the Lord said, "Let there be crap."

56
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,240
[BUZZING]

57
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,080
[CHATTERING]

58
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,920
[CHATTERS]

59
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:59,900
- -and thereby reducing
the number of states to 49.

60
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,480
Cool. It's the NBC News feed.

61
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,820
Mm, feed.

62
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,960
You get to see what they do
during breaks.

63
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:10,910
We'll be right back with a special report
on soccer moms who hate soccer.

64
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:15,040
STAGEHAND: Clear.
- Oh, Lord, I'm so fat, aah.

65
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:17,820
[VOMITING]

66
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:24,250
Hey, Lis, wanna try some satellite TV?
We've got Japanese <i>Friends.</i>

67
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:26,100
[INSTRUMENTAL FRIENDS THEME
PLAYING]

68
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,870
Do you like my new shirt?

69
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:35,030
It says, "Reggae Hairstyle Rock 'n' Roll."
Could I be more Japanese?

70
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:38,010
You are the emperor of last year.

71
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,270
Your comeback shames me.

72
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:41,700
How about The Clock Channel?

73
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:44,250
ANNOUNCER: <i>Coming up on
The Clock Channel: 6:00.</i>

74
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,990
Wait a minute, I saw this one.

75
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:49,840
I have to study for the elementary school
achievement test, and so do you.

76
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:52,380
Hey, I don't have to study
on the weekend.

77
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:54,100
It's Wednesday night.

78
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:57,740
Kids, kids, you're both right.

79
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,630
- Mm.
LISA: Oh.

80
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,630
MAN [ON TV]: <i>We're back with </i>Who
Wants to Marry an Internet Billionaire?

81
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:05,730
<i>Uh, no, millionaire.</i>
<i>Oh, well, now he's broke.</i>

82
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,630
[BOTH GROANING]

83
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:18,530
Why don't you turn off the TV
and join us for dessert?

84
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,810
I made a pie.

85
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:22,610
Put pie here.

86
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,820
[SIGHS]

87
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,090
Would you like some ice cream
with that?

88
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:29,780
Me not pig.

89
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:35,230
MAN [ON TV]:
<i>We now return to </i>Robo Trouble.

90
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,930
<i>Oh, I'm sorry. I mean, </i>Robot Rumble.

91
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,620
[GRUNTING]

92
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,730
[IN ROBOTIC VOICE]
Why are we fighting each other?

93
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,830
Together we can defeat the humans
and rule the Earth.

94
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,680
[IN ROBOTIC VOICE]
I agree.

95
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,060
[ALL GASP]

96
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,520
[SCREAMS]

97
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,270
<i>Sucker.</i>

98
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:57,630
[LAUGHS]

99
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,950
Homicidal robots. So like us.

100
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,400
[SNORING]

101
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:06,500
Bart, the test is in two hours
and you haven't slept in a fortnight.

102
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:09,650
- What's a fortnight?
- You should know. It's on the test.

103
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:13,110
[GRUNTS]

104
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,750
KRABAPPEL:
No pressure, children.

105
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:19,530
These test results will follow you for the
rest of your life and beyond the grave.

106
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:24,760
BART: <i>This test is boring.
What else is on?</i>

107
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:34,290
[VOMITING]

108
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,640
[CHUCKLES]

109
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:47,150
It's finally happened, Bart.

110
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:49,740
You've lost your mind.

111
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,540
[ALL SINGING "HAVA NAGILA"]

112
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,790
[LAUGHS]

113
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,900
SKINNER:
Now, let's raise the roof...

114
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:15,340
...for the bland informative rap
of M.C. Safety and the Caution Crew.

115
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:18,170
Yo, yo, yo, y'all feeling cautious?

116
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,190
[RAPPING]
<i>I say a crosswalk, a cross-ity walk</i>

117
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,390
<i>And don't stop crossing</i>
<i>Till you're on the next block</i>

118
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,630
<i>First you look both ways</i>
<i>Then you walk not run</i>

119
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:27,400
<i>Obeying safety rules is acceptable
fun</i> <i>Break it down now</i>

120
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:30,380
<i>Just walk, don't run</i>
<i>Drink juice, yum-yum</i>

121
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,180
[LAUGHS]

122
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,570
Watch out, Beatles.

123
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:37,170
I have one more important
announcement to share with you.

124
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,470
Would Lisa Simpson join me on stage?

125
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,900
Oh?

126
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:44,720
Lisa, because of your outstanding score
on yesterday's big test...

127
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:48,240
...you're being immediately moved up
to the third grade.

128
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:51,230
[CROWD CHEERING]

129
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:52,670
She's not so great.

130
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,210
She got diarrhea when we went
to Carlsbad Caverns.

131
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,440
[ALL LAUGHING]

132
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,640
[SHOUTS]

133
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,560
Okay, Bart...

134
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:04,690
...since you like attention so much,
I have a second announcement.

135
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,290
[CHATTERING]

136
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,330
I was going to tell you this privately...

137
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:10,970
...but because of your incredibly low
test score...

138
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,690
...we're sending you back to third grade.

139
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,130
[ALL LAUGHING]

140
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:18,150
Huh?

141
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,740
What?
I gotta be in the same class as her?

142
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:23,590
What?
I gotta be in the same class as him?

143
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:28,820
Hmm? They're gonna be
in the same class as each other?

144
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:30,600
[GASPS]

145
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,920
An old Army buddy is
visiting <i>Mannix?</i>

146
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:39,270
Class, meet our newest third graders,
Lisa and Bart Simpson.

147
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,630
Lisa comes to us from Miss Hoover...

148
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:46,360
...while Bart was taught
by Mrs. Krabappel. Slut.

149
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,930
[IN UNISON]
Hi, Bart and Lisa.

150
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:54,390
A rooster sits on a roof facing north.
It lays an egg. Which way does it roll?

151
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,130
Okay, the sun rises in the east...

152
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:00,160
...so the rooster would probably
wanna lay it on the cool side...

153
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:03,000
Roosters don't lay eggs. They're boys.

154
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:05,170
- Very good, Bart.
- Mm-hm.

155
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:09,610
Lisa, I want you to stick close
to your big brother until you catch up.

156
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:14,520
[SIGHS]

157
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,520
[NELSON CHUCKLES]

158
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,010
Young man, you're not in this class.

159
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:21,610
- What are you doing here?
- Laughing at jerks.

160
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,610
Quiet nerds burp only near school.

161
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:31,790
Bart, I'm doing
my geography homework.

162
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,840
That's how you remember
the four original provinces of Canada.

163
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,790
"Quebec, New Brunswick,
Ontario, Nova Scotia."

164
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,040
Quiet nerds burp only near school.

165
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,370
Here's how you remember
their principle exports:

166
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,450
Dogs eat barf solely on Wednesday,
Mabel.

167
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:47,230
Stop. I wanna learn on my own.

168
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,440
[VENT OPENS]

169
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:50,670
Canada's governors general:

170
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,420
Clowns love haircuts,
so should Lee Marvin's valet.

171
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,750
Get out!

172
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:00,570
Here are your math tests.
Morgan, Dakota, Ashley...

173
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:05,110
...Dakota, Tyler, Tyler, Lisa.

174
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,590
What's this weird mark next to my A?

175
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:08,950
That's an A-minus.

176
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:10,580
Mm, minus?

177
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:11,970
Nice work, Bart.

178
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,320
An A? Copacetic.

179
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,240
You did better than me?

180
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,990
Eh, I took this test last year.
The answer key never changes.

181
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:22,930
B-C-B-C-A-A-B-B-C-C-D. False. False.
True. William Jennings Bryan.

182
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:25,630
That's cheating. Bart cheated.

183
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:29,420
Young lady, in the third grade,
we don't care for tattletales.

184
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,200
[GROANS]

185
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:33,030
And we don't care for moaners either.

186
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:34,880
[SOBS]

187
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:37,810
Sobbing only pushes
Bart's grade higher.

188
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,870
[SOBS]

189
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,930
OTTO:
Pukers in back.

190
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:46,130
Kids, look what I got you
for your third-grade field trip.

191
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,720
Matching fanny packs.

192
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,530
Now your fannies match.

193
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,080
[BOTH GROANING]

194
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,310
[GRUNTS]

195
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,600
- Hey, get away from me. Get...
- Get away.

196
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,870
- Quit it.
- Stop it. Let go.

197
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,740
Stop. You'll crush your juice boxes.

198
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,890
BOTH:
Oh.

199
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:06,900
[BOTH GRUNTING]

200
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:09,980
All right, everybody choose a buddy
for the field trip.

201
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:12,270
- I'll take Kyle.
- I'll take Ashley.

202
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:15,560
Saying your buddy's name out loud
is a security risk.

203
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,370
I'll just put you two together.

204
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,150
BOTH:
Oh.

205
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:21,860
<i>[TONY BENNETT'S "CAPITAL CITY"</i>
<i>PLAYING]</i>

206
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:26,810
<i>There's a swingin' town I know</i>
<i>Called Capital City</i>

207
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:30,330
- Punch buggy red, unh.
- Ow.

208
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,160
You are such an immature...

209
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,380
- Punch buggy white, unh.
- Ow.

210
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:36,170
- Stop fighting.
- He started it.

211
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:37,890
He did punch buggy first.

212
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,290
What's punch buggy?

213
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:42,380
When you see a Volkswagen Bug,
you punch somebody and yell the color.

214
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:43,800
[CHATTERING]

215
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,380
[ALL GASPING]

216
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:47,550
BOY 1: Punch buggy blue.
BOY 2: Ow.

217
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,080
GIRL 1: Punch buggy green.
BOY 3: Oh.

218
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,740
BOY 4: Punch buggy taupe.
BOY 5: Ow.

219
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,350
Oh, that really hurt.

220
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:53,800
[THUDDING]

221
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:55,000
OTTO:
Two for flinching.

222
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:56,370
[THUDS]

223
00:11:56,720 --> 00:12:00,090
[ALL WHIMPERING]

224
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,570
Now, as we cross the street, I want you
to hold hands with your buddy.

225
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,950
[BOTH GROANING]

226
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:11,760
Hey, dude, who's your girlfriend?

227
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:13,360
[ALL LAUGHING]

228
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,910
Did you see his face?

229
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,790
Well, what happened, dude?
Did your girlfriend dump you?

230
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:23,300
[ALL LAUGHING]

231
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,400
[BOTH GROANING]

232
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:28,160
Now, children, if you look up
at the capitol dome...

233
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:31,800
...you'll see a mural of our state bird,
the pot-bellied sparrow...

234
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:34,050
...eating our state pasta, bowtie.

235
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,560
[CHILDREN GROANING]

236
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,920
MAN:
Order, order, order.

237
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:41,900
The chair recognizes the esteemed
representative from Capital City.

238
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:45,190
BART:
The Capital City Goofball?

239
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,660
That's right. To win, he spent 80 million
from his own pocket.

240
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:52,330
GOOFBALL: Mr. Speaker, the time
has come to redesign our state flag.

241
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,850
This Confederate symbol
is an embarrassment...

242
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,810
...particularly as we are
a northern state.

243
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,230
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

244
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,600
This lively debate
has given me an idea.

245
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:05,730
Tonight, each buddy team
is going to design a new state flag.

246
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:09,140
Homework on a field trip?
What have you been huffing?

247
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:13,630
Well, Bart's being his usual jerky self.

248
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,760
But, Mom, I'm really excited
about this new flag design.

249
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:20,340
Oh, and the hotel gives you
a free <i>USA Today </i>outside your room.

250
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,430
No, I'm sure it's free.

251
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,100
Okay, I won't touch it.

252
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,780
Well, make sure you don't.

253
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:28,930
And try not to let your brother
get under your skin, honey.

254
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:32,470
Believe me, he doesn't.
His act is getting old fast.

255
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,590
He thinks he's really cool.

256
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:39,780
<i>But frankly, the other kids are starting</i>
<i>to wake up and smell the cooties.</i>

257
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:43,140
One last sunbeam and we're done.

258
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:45,260
"To fraternal love."

259
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:48,730
When I get through with that flag,
it's gonna be a Bart-mangled banner.

260
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:54,690
So I understand you children
have some state flags for me.

261
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:57,570
- Who would like to go first?
- We would, Governor Bailey.

262
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,330
- Team Simpson.
- I spearheaded this one.

263
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,260
I'll just unfurl this.

264
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,170
[SCREAMING]

265
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:09,960
[GASPS]

266
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,460
That was my worst unfurling ever.

267
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:15,450
Lisa, how could you?
The governor is crying.

268
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,750
[SOBBING]

269
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,820
Oh.

270
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:22,270
[NELSON LAUGHS]

271
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,970
You weren't on this field trip.
How did you get here?

272
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:26,390
Biked.

273
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,930
Bart, I am so mad at you.

274
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:36,140
Ha-ha-ha. You should've seen the look
on your face. It was like this:

275
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:38,370
[BART LAUGHS]

276
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:40,340
[GROWLS]

277
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,720
[GRUNTING]

278
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:48,530
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

279
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:51,330
[BOTH GRUNTING]

280
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:52,680
[BUS HORN HONKS]

281
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,560
- Huh?
- Oh, the bus.

282
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:57,000
[CHATTERING]

283
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:58,690
Okay, children, before we leave...

284
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:01,220
- ...is anyone missing their buddy?
- No.

285
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:04,280
Ah, the buddy system, foolproof.

286
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,590
Floor it, Otto.

287
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:11,840
LISA:
Wait! Wait!

288
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,080
[BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY]

289
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:17,410
- Ha, ha, they left without you.
- They left without you too, you idiot.

290
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:20,900
If I'm an idiot, how come
I'm the smartest kid in the third grade?

291
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:23,370
Because you've already done it once.

292
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:27,270
- You've lost me.
- Oh, forget it.

293
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:30,300
- Hey, how do we get back?
- No problem.

294
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:33,750
We'll just circle around like those kids
in <i>The Blair Witch Project.</i>

295
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:39,590
I must be getting close.
I recognize that girl.

296
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:46,720
- Oh, Bart, I think we're lost.
- I used to be lost.

297
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:50,660
Until a friend turned me onto a book.
A book that changed my life.

298
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,000
It's called, <i>Lisa is Stupid.</i>

299
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:56,140
- You die now.
- Aah? Whoa.

300
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:58,230
Hey!

301
00:15:58,680 --> 00:15:59,840
[BART CHUCKLES]

302
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,400
[McCONNELL SOBBING]

303
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,540
They're gone.
I don't know what happened.

304
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:08,370
If the buddy system can fail,
I don't know what to believe in.

305
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,630
There, there, Audrey.
It's happened to all of us.

306
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,410
Willie, we have two more names
for the wall.

307
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,490
[WEEPS]

308
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:21,210
Why is it always the kids
with the long names?

309
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,600
[DOORBELL RINGS]

310
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:32,670
- Hello, Principal Skinner.
- A parent who waives the right to sue...

311
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:34,290
- ...says what?
- What?

312
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,530
- Got it.
- Hey, you can't fool us.

313
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:38,330
We're from the Learn to Fart state.

314
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:39,630
[SIGHS]

315
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:42,940
Bart and Lisa are lost in Capital City
and presumed crying.

316
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,770
Huh! My poor babies.

317
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:49,050
I'm so sorry.
Lisa's a very special little girl.

318
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:52,060
And we'll spare no expense
in finding her.

319
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:54,250
- What about Bart?
- We're looking.

320
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:57,280
But in the meantime, the class clown
pro tem will take his place.

321
00:16:57,840 --> 00:16:59,420
Cowabunga.

322
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,630
[LISA SHUDDERING]

323
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,040
- You cold?
- What do you care?

324
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,160
- Here.
- Thanks.

325
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,170
Where'd you get...? Oh.

326
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:17,100
Bart, you're my big brother.
You should act like it more often.

327
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:20,500
You know, protect me
from the bad things in the world.

328
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:24,800
Well, as far as nerdy little sisters go,
you're the coolest.

329
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:28,180
- Thanks, Bart.
- And I'm sorry I sabotaged your flag.

330
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,440
I'm sorry I got us lost out here.

331
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:33,720
Oh, and I'm sorry I sawed the heads off
your Malibu Stacy dolls.

332
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:36,490
- Okay, you go.
- I don't think I've done anything else.

333
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,950
Okay, I'll go again. Remember when
your bike was mangled by "gypsies"?

334
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:42,520
- Yes.
- Yeah, funny story.

335
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,300
One day, I was really bored...

336
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:47,280
...and Dad had left a steamroller
idling in the driveway...

337
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,640
This is where the kids were last seen.

338
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:53,230
Aah! The plastic casing
from the tip of Bart's shoelace.

339
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:56,090
A mother knows.

340
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:59,010
Well, he's not gonna get very far
without that.

341
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:02,230
- Bart, is that you?
MAN: No.

342
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:07,240
[GUNS COCK]

343
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:08,470
[BOTH GASP]

344
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:09,640
Say your prayers.

345
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,890
Oh, Lord, please strike
these mountain folk dead.

346
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:14,110
Bart. Listen, we're really sorry.

347
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:16,770
We got lost on a field trip
from Springfield Elementary.

348
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:20,300
Lost on a field trip?
Heck, why didn't you say so?

349
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:23,270
That's how Grandpappy
wound up in these parts.

350
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:27,560
They was taking us to Capital City
to see <i>The Nutcracker.</i>

351
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:30,210
And I wandered away from the group...

352
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:33,380
...married a bear
and I started up my family.

353
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,500
I told you, I ain't a bear.

354
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:36,760
[CHUCKLES]

355
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:38,240
Roar, roar, roar.

356
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,530
No one understands you, She-Bear.

357
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,300
[LAUGHS]

358
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:48,050
- Thanks for driving us back to town.
- No problem.

359
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:51,050
We were going there anyway
to pick up the new <i>Spy </i>magazine.

360
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:53,700
I'm sorry,
they don't publish that anymore.

361
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:57,390
The world I grewed up in is gone.

362
00:18:58,040 --> 00:19:00,070
[MARGE GROANING]

363
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,320
Oh, my special little guys.

364
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:05,600
You're okay. You're okay.

365
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:08,690
And, Maggie, you no longer
have to live with the burden...

366
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:12,050
...of replacing Bart and Lisa.

367
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:15,890
If this episode
has taught us anything...

368
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:18,320
...it's that nothing works better
than the status quo.

369
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,290
- You're back to the fourth grade.
- Yay!

370
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:23,110
And, Lisa, you have a choice.

371
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:25,510
You may continue
to be challenged in third grade...

372
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,770
...or return to second grade
and be merely a big fish in a small pond.

373
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:30,340
Big fish. Big fish.

374
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:31,730
[ALL GROANING]

375
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:34,080
The status quo.

376
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:37,970
The status quo? <i>Ay caramba.</i>

377
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:40,320
That's just sad.

378
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,610
WOMAN:
Shh.

379
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:33,320
[English - US -SDH]